## 4. Deletion mechanisms

- Soft-delete on request or account closure; hard-delete and backup-rotation pruning within the declared retention period.
- For data held only for archival in the public interest, scientific research, or statistical purposes (Art. 89), retention may be longer but pseudonymisation/aggregation MUST be applied.
- Right to erasure (Art. 17) overrides scheduled retention where the conditions of Art. 17(1) are met.

